  "texts": [
    "From Table 5, we can observe that:• The absence of either of the two learning mechanisms would result in a decline in performance, thereby indicating that both learning mechanisms have contributed to the enhancement of long-term engagement.",
    "• Based on the experimental details presented in Section 5.1.4, the aforementioned improvements are achieved using only 100 episodes of data for both learning mechanisms.",
    "This suggests the high efficiency of in-context learning compared to fine-tuning and training from scratch.",
    "Effects of Critic Module (RQ3)In this subsection, our objective is to demonstrate the effectiveness of the Critic module in estimating the state-value function, denoted as 𝑉 𝜋 (𝑠), which is crucial for facilitating the update process of the Actor module.",
    "The state-value function 𝑉 𝜋 (𝑠) gives the expected cumulative discounted reward if we start from state 𝑠 and act according to the policy.To get an accurate and unbiased estimation of 𝑉 𝜋 (𝑠), for a specific state 𝑠, we sample 1000 complete trajectories according to the Actor policy and calculate the cumulative discounted reward for each trajectory."
